<t>
<field>ACTIVITY.CODE</field>
<desc>
            <p>In order to allow the Forex application to produce multiple types of delivery advices which will depend on the contract activity, customer type and the currency type. </p>
            <p />
            <p>Contract Activity </p>
            <p>The activity may be initial input, maturity, reversal, takedown or amendment. </p>
            <p />
            <p>Customer Type </p>
            <p>Based on the counterparty of the deal, which may be a BANK or a CLIENT. </p>
            <p />
            <p>Currency Type </p>
            <p>If one of the currencies involved in the deal is a precious metal, indicated by the field PRECIOUS.METAL in the CURRENCY record, the deal is treated as a metal deal, otherwise it is a currency deal. </p>
            <p>Each combination of these elements will correspond to an activity code. </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>Free Formatted.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
